                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d356">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94 Commission/542: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Geneva (<persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1"
                            type="from">Gilbert</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-11-21T15:00:00+01:00"
                            >November 21, 1932—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received November 21—1:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>328. <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_LERB1">Lytton</persName> report considered
                    in Council meeting this morning. With the exception of the President who gave a
                    brief résumé of status of the question the only speaker was the Japanese
                    representative who reiterated substantially the arguments contained in the
                    printed observations of Japanese Government, a document comprising 39 foolscap
                    pages circulated by the Secretariat yesterday. Copies are being forwarded by
                        mail.<note n="25" xml:id="d356fn25">League of Nations, <hi rend="italic"
                            >Official Journal</hi>, Special Supplement No. 111, p. 88.</note>
                    Consider it probable that the Department has already received the text of the
                    Japanese observations from a Japanese source. If not, and summary is desired,
                    please instruct.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_VSRG1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Gilbert</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
